@prefix : <#> .
@prefix schema: <http://schema.org/> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix prov: <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#> .
@prefix cert: <http://www.w3.org/ns/auth/cert#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix onto: <../ontology.ttl#> .
@prefix skills: <https://github.com/OpenLinkSoftware/ai-agent-skills/tree/main/> .

<> a schema:CreativeWork ;
    schema:about :youidValidationGates ;
    schema:name "YouID Skill — Validation Gates"@en ;
    schema:description "Standing validation gates for the youid skill, ensuring credential consistency across all identity output documents."@en ;
    schema:dateCreated "2026-06-18T13:05:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

:youidValidationGates a schema:HowTo ;
    schema:name "YouID Credential Validation Procedure"@en ;
    schema:description "Post-generation and pre-deployment checks for WebID credential bundles generated by the youid skill."@en ;
    schema:step :gate-pkcs12PublicKeyConsistency .

:gate-pkcs12PublicKeyConsistency a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 1 ;
    schema:name "Basic WebID Test — PKCS#12 Public Key Consistency Gate"@en ;
    schema:text """
Critical validation gate. Before deploying or distributing any YouID credential bundle, verify that the RSA public key found in the PKCS#12 certificate (`cert.p12`) is correctly and consistently reflected in all three local output documents:

1. `index.html` — verify modulus (cert:modulus RDFa) and exponent (cert:exponent RDFa) match the cert
2. `profile.ttl` — verify cert:modulus and cert:exponent values match the cert; exponent must use "65537"^^xsd:int typed literal
3. `profile.jsonld` — verify cert:modulus and cert:exponent values match the cert

Procedure:
  a) Extract modulus and exponent from cert.p12:
     openssl pkcs12 -in cert.p12 -passin pass:youid -nokeys -clcerts | openssl x509 -noout -modulus
     openssl pkcs12 -in cert.p12 -passin pass:youid -nokeys -clcerts | openssl x509 -noout -text | awk '/Exponent:/ {print $2}'
  b) Search each file for the matching modulus hex string and exponent value
  c) All three must match. Any discrepancy means the generation script has a bug and must be fixed before deployment.
  d) If CA/issuer certificates are in the chain, repeat the check for the end-entity (leaf) cert only.

Historical bug: On 2026-06-18, generate_certificate.sh:107 had a grep -A1 bug that captured "X509v3extensions:" instead of the real exponent, corrupting all output files. The fix was awk '/Exponent:/ {print $2}'.

Also critical: the exponent in profile.ttl and public_key.ttl MUST use "65537"^^xsd:int typed literal format, not bare "65537" (xsd:integer). Some SPARQL processors require strict xsd:int type matching for cert:exponent.
"""@en ;
    onto:hasTrigger onto:triggerSkillInvocation, onto:triggerArtifactGeneration ;
    schema:associatedMedia skills:youid#this ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <../sessions/2026-06-18-opencode-agent-skills.ttl> .
